| Simpler                                         | More statistically informed                                 |
| Faster training                                 | Slower training                                             |
| GPT family commonly uses BPE-based tokenization | BERT uses WordPiece                                         |

What is WordPiece?

"WordPiece is a subword tokenization algorithm developed by Google and used in BERT. Unlike BPE, which merges the most frequent adjacent symbol pairs, WordPiece selects subwords that maximize the probability of the training data. 
This usually produces more meaningful subwords and improves language understanding, making it well suited for tasks such as masked language modeling, text classification, and question answering."
